Emilia: [...Priscilla, do you feel the same way?]

Priscilla remained silent, not responding to Emilia's question.

However, to Emilia, it had felt as if that silence was saying that she shared Emilia's opinion that Abel hated Subaru.

Emilia: [Priscilla, do you know why? Up until a little while ago, you were talking to Abel and the others, weren't you?]

Priscilla: [Unfortunately, the discussion that had kept mineself back had no relation to your foolish commoner. Fragments that have broken off like that foolish commoner do not become the subject of conversation...no, having heard the tale of the Great Disaster which destroyed the Demon City, mineself will not say it was completely unrelated to that foolish commoner]

Emilia: [Of the Demon City... Ah, then, you were talking to Yorna? To Priscilla's mother]

In the middle of the discussion in the large chamber, the topic of the parent-child relationship between Yorna and Priscilla had come up. In the end, it had been swept away by the matter of how Louis should be handled that arose later, but that probably would not have happened for the people involved.

Naturally, the reunited mother and child should have discussed it.

Emilia: [Still, I was also surprised. That Priscilla also had half demi-human blood...]

Priscilla: [Nonsense. Do not equate mineself with you. I think it surely must not be the case, but did you draw close to me because you had felt an affinity over that?]

Emilia: [That wasn't it at all, but is it not true? Then, is Yorna-san Priscilla's foster parent? If that were so, that would also be surprising. After all, I also…]

Priscilla: [Nonsense, do not make me repeat mineself, nonsense. That too, is your rashness.]

Emilia: [Ehh? Then, what do you mean?]

If Yorna and her were biologically parent and child, her foxkin blood should be flowing inside Priscilla, but that had been denied.

If you were then to think that meant a foster parent, that had also been flatly denied.

Emilia, being a half-elf and raised by her mother, a dear aunt by blood named Fortuna, had thought Priscilla was the same in some ways.

Emilia: [Not blood related, and not a foster parent ...in that case, how is she your mother?]

Priscilla: [Is there any reason why mineself must explain everything to you?]

Emilia: [No, I don't think so. But if you don't tell me, I'll be reaaally curious]

Knowing it was selfish, Emilia had tried asking Priscilla for the truth. The possibility had been high that just as she had rejected a friendly relationship, she would refuse her an answer.

However, Priscilla was silent for a moment, and then,

Priscilla: [――Iris and the King of Thorns]

Emilia: [Eh? ]

Priscilla: [It is an old story. Do you know it?]

Emilia: [Well, I do know it. Umm, Lady Petra likes that kind of thing]

Emilia's eyes widened as she nodded at the words that had abruptly left Priscilla's lips.

She had been taught that "Iris and the King of Thorns” was an old story that had been passed down from long, long ago, and was a historical account that originated from the Vollachian Empire.

Emilia had also heard no more than a brief outline of the story, but it seemed like it was a love story between an emperor of Vollachia from long ago called the "King of Thorns," and a girl named "Iris.]

Unfortunately, Emilia had ended up saying that she still did not really understand why it was interesting but――,

Emilia: [What is the issue with that story? Is it a story that Priscilla likes?]

Priscilla: [It seems you are a half-devil who cannot understand things from context. Naturally, it is bound to be related to the flow of the conversation thus far]

Emilia: [Thus far...Yorna and Priscilla's parent-child relationship and this old story?]

Priscilla: [――Iris and the King of Thorns had joined hands to bring about an end to a civil war that had swallowed up many races in the Empire However, right before the pair that were linked heart-to-heart could be wedded, they experienced a betrayal, and the story ends.

Emilia: [...A sad story, isn't it.]

As the corners of her eyebrows dropped, Emilia muttered the gist of the story Priscilla had told.

It was very disheartening when people who have worked their hardest are not rewarded. Just as she despaired at the situation the Emperor of Vollachia was placed in now, she held the same feelings for the end of the couple that had already been made into a story.

At Emilia's reaction, Priscilla exhaled with a "Ha",

Priscilla: [However, the story and the facts of history differ. In the histories, having lost Iris to betrayal, the "King of Thorns" descended into madness, and decided to eradicate the wolfmen and molemen that had raised their blades. For the few that had escaped, in the Empire, even now, they are burned at the stake as soon as they are found]

Emilia: [It's understandable to be angry about that but ...... still, for people in this day and age]

Priscilla: [It has nothing to do with them, does it? You should be no stranger to that, having been persecuted as a half-devil yourself]

Emilia: [――――]

The sharpness of Priscilla's phrasing had stung, but Emilia's skin was hard as iron against that sort of bad-mouthing. However, even if she did not bleed, the pain of being struck remained the same.

As she would properly complain about that later, Emilia was more curious about where things went from there in the rest of Priscilla's story.

What had the King of Thorns done after losing Iris and taking revenge on the traitor?

Emilia: [With that, is the story of the King of Thorns over?]

Priscilla: [――. With having merely given in to anger, you could not possibly say that was having descended into madness. Thus, after that, the King of Thorns had directed his madness towards Iris, who had been lost]

Emilia: [Towards Iris?]

Raising her eyebrows at the story's unexpected course of events, Emilia repeated back the words she had heard. Priscilla nodded at those words and turned her crimson eyes to the sky.

Frustrated, Emilia's lips trembled as she sought Priscilla's next words.

Emilia: [What did the King of Thorns do to Iris?]

Priscilla: [He laid a curse upon her]

Emilia: [A curse? That's...]

Was that something one would lay on someone precious to them, much less someone whose loss caused them suffering?

Indifferent to those doubts of Emilia's, Priscilla spoke of the details of the curse.

That was――,

Priscilla: [――The secret art of dragging a perished soul back down to earth without handing it over to Od Lagna]

Emilia: [The soul, of a dead person?]

Priscilla: [It is said that there is a secret art called "Sacrament of the Immortal King" which can even revive the dead, but its existence is considered questionable. However, this "Commandment of Thorns" is a curse born of insatiable yearning.]

The story of the dead coming back to life is astounding, but what is important here is not that, but the other "curse" as they called it.

The subject of the souls of the dead and their fate was also discussed at the Pleiades Watchtower through the " Books of the Dead," in which the memories of the deceased were imprinted within them.

The existence of the "Books of the Dead" convinced them of the existence of the soul within humans.

Emilia: [But, what does it mean to drag down a soul? Does it mean they come back to life?]

Priscilla: [It does not work that way. Iris's body was torn apart after her death, and even if her soul returned, it would not bring her back to life. In the first place, the Commandment of Thorn has no such power.]

Emilia: [Then what would happen? If there was no body――]

Where would the soul go if there is no place for the returning soul to enter?

In response to Emilia's question, Priscilla quietly lowered her gaze. Instead of looking at the sky, her crimson eyes looked into Emilia's amethyst ones, and――

Priscilla: [It is settled upon. If the soul does not return to Od Laguna, it will return to the world where it will not receive its intended treatment and will enter its next vessel. ――It is a rebirth or a reincarnation.]

Emilia: [――――]

Priscilla: [As long as the curse is not broken, as long as the Commandment of thorns that entangles them is not lifted, the reincarnation of the departed soul will repeat. Again and again, it will repeat itself, repeating life and death over and over again. ――One of these lives, the life before Yorna Mishigure, was my dear mother's.]

△▼△▼△▼△

Abel: [――Sandra Benedict, that caught me by surprise.]

Yorna: [My Lord, you were the one who hid Prisca from me, you were the one who is a bad person.]

Hard, cold voices collided with each other, and quiet heat intermingled in a stone room.

Both of them looked at each other and chose their words as if they were searching each other's hearts. Abel, removed the Oni mask covering his face and revealing his true face, and Yorna, puffed purple smoke from her kiseru.


Until just now, there was also a third "Priscilla" there.

However, as soon as she deemed that she had concluded the essential discussions, she immediately left this place. Abel accepted this attitude, but it did not dissuade Yorna from being upset.

Of course. ――The mistress of the Demon City cannot easily accept the change in her own biological child.

Yorna: [Why not both honestly admit that our secrecy has been a detriment to each other?]

Abel: [I had my reasons for keeping it a secret. Even you can understand that.]

Yorna: [――. That's true, I guess.]

At Abel's answer, Yorna ponders, her eyes downcast and her long eyelashes quivering.

The unexpected encounter with Priscilla sent a huge ripple through Yorna's heart. It was a reality that Yorna had never expected, or even hoped for, for it was never going to come true.

For Yorna, it must have been a great joy to see Priscilla alive and well, and for Abel, it must have been a terrible gamble.

The idea that Priscilla is Prisca and that she would be alive is unthinkable.

There is no doubt that Abel's involvement was behind that unthinkable event.

Yorna: [What is my Lord doing――?]

Abel: [――I promised you the means to break the commandment of the thorn. If you want the answer to your question, I have no reason to grant you any other reward.]

Yorna: [――――]

Straight away, Abel rejected Yorna's challenge.

When Abel refuses to reveal the answer, forcing Yorna to weigh it against her greatest wish.

For a long, long time now, she has lived and died many times, and she has continued to view the world with this soul.

Even though she could barely remember the face of that person anymore, that's why――

Abel: [Yorna Mishigure ――no, Iris, who the King of Thorns fell in love with at first sight.]

Yes, Yorna's name, a name that beloved man, long ago, called her many times, by a man who is many generations removed from the blood of her beloved man.

Abel: [Raise your spirits even higher. For your dearest wish and, above all - Prisca Benedict, to keep your supposedly lost daughter alive in the future.]

In a voice so cold that it could not be compared to that of her beloved, he insisted.


